# Fusion Cell Marketing Website — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is the forward-facing marketing website for Fusion Cell, a dedicated team-based management service for high-net-worth principals with complex lifestyle holdings. Pure HTML/CSS/JS static site — no frameworks, no build tools, no Tailwind.

## Core Philosophy
The product is the Fusion Cell team — directors, managers, and specialists. The app is the communication gateway between the principal and their team. The team is the engine; the app is the window. Never position the app as the primary product.

## Tech Stack
- HTML5 semantic markup
- CSS3 with custom properties (defined in css/variables.css)
- Vanilla JavaScript only
- Google Fonts (Inter) via CDN
- No React, Next.js, Tailwind, or build tools

## Brand System

### Colors (all defined in css/variables.css)
- Backgrounds: #000000, #0a0a0a, #111111
- Surfaces: #161616 to #1a1a1a
- Borders: #222222 to #2a2a2a
- Accent: #4ade80 (mint green), hover #22c55e
- Text: #ffffff (primary), #a1a1aa (secondary), #71717a (muted)

### Typography
- Inter only, weights 400/500/600/700
- Tight letter-spacing on headlines (-0.02em to -0.03em)
- Line height 1.6-1.7 on body text for dark background readability

### Design Principles
- Private banking aesthetic, NOT SaaS product page
- Generous whitespace (120-160px section padding desktop)
- Restrained mint green usage — CTAs, subtle highlights, hover states only
- Glass morphism on nav (subtle backdrop-blur)
- Scroll reveals: 20-30px translate up, opacity fade, 0.6s ease-out
- Always respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Terminology Rules — NON-NEGOTIABLE

### Always say:
- "your Fusion Cell team" (not admins, staff, operators, the system)
- "directors and managers" (not users, employees)
- "the app" or "the Fusion Cell app" (not platform, tool, software, portal)
- "holdings" (not assets — on the marketing site)
- "your team uploads / manages / maintains" (not the system generates)
- "customizable" or "tailored to you" (not one-size-fits-all)
- "window into your team's work" (not automated solution)
- "cash flow" (not bills)
- "principal" or "you" (not client, user, customer)

### Never say:
- "portfolio" (implies securities/investment)
- "automated", "AI-driven", "AI-powered" (AI assistant is a feature, not the identity)
- "smart" or "intelligent" to describe the core service

## What NOT to Do
- No JavaScript frameworks or build tools
- No Tailwind CSS
- No stock photography
- No backend functionality (contact form is front-end only)
- No SaaS patterns (pricing tables, feature grids, "Start Free Trial")
- No bright colors except mint green accent, used sparingly
- No Phantom Services branding — Fusion Cell is its own entity

## Code Style
- Use CSS custom properties from variables.css for all colors, radii, transitions
- Semantic HTML with proper heading hierarchy
- ARIA labels where needed
- All hover states use var(--transition-base) for smooth transitions
- Mobile breakpoint: 768px, tablet: 768-1199px, desktop: 1200px+

## Messaging (March 2026 revision)
- Lead with the PROBLEM (fragmentation, time tax, complexity) not the solution
- Fusion Cell REPLACES chaos — it doesn't ADD a layer
- "One relationship" is the core message
- Two modes: Family (managed services) and Business (executive visibility)
- The principal stops being the integration layer
- Daily Executive Brief + 24/7 portal = decisions, not audits
- $14.4B managed to date — use for credibility
- AES-256 encryption — use in security sections